{"type":"text","timestamp":1773352286995,"sessionID":"ses_31bfcf566ffeX54k1gNGv0ej46","part":{"id":"prt_ce4080458001K4TI3J39IiPvpJ","sessionID":"ses_31bfcf566ffeX54k1gNGv0ej46","messageID":"msg_ce407fa8a001DBhzmMjnYxgNpM","type":"text","text":"## Goal\n\nImplement \"Agent Browser\" integration for the `wombo-combo` AI agent orchestration system. The feature gives agents real browser capabilities for testing web applications — supporting browser-based verification as part of the build/verify pipeline, with isolated browser instances per agent and headless operation for CI environments.\n\n## Instructions\n\n- **Feature ID:** `agent-browser-integration`, **Branch:** `feature/agent-browser-integration`, **Base:** `main`\n- Must support browser-based verification as part of the build/verify pipeline\n- Must isolate browser instances per agent (no shared state between concurrent agents)\n- Must support headless operation for CI environments\n- Use conventional commits with scope `agent-browser-integration`\n- Commit after each logical unit of work (roughly per subtask)\n- Do NOT squash all changes into one commit\n- Do NOT push to remote — the orchestrator handles that\n- Do NOT modify `.features.yml` — the orchestrator handles that\n- After completing all changes, run `bun run build` to verify everything works\n- The project uses Bun runtime, TypeScript strict mode, ESM only\n- No heavy npm dependencies (puppeteer/playwright) — uses system-installed browsers via child_process with Chrome DevTools Protocol\n\n## Discoveries\n\n- The project is `wombo-combo` — an AI agent orchestration system for parallel feature development\n- Architecture follows a clear pattern: `src/config.ts` (types + defaults), `src/lib/*.ts` (core logic), `src/commands/*.ts` (CLI commands), `src/index.ts` (CLI entry point + arg parsing), `src/lib/schema.ts` (command schema registry for introspection)\n- The verification pipeline is: agent completes → `handleBuildVerification()` in `launch.ts` calls `runBuild()` from `verifier.ts` → on pass, auto-merge → on fail, retry with error context\n- `WomboConfig` in `config.ts` has a `DEFAULT_CONFIG` object that must be updated alongside the type interface\n- The `config.ts` `deepMerge` function handles partial config from `wombo.json`\n- `schema.ts` has a declarative command/flag registry (~541 lines) that needs to stay in sync with `index.ts` arg parsing\n- The `handleBuildVerification` function in `launch.ts` is shared by `verify.ts`, `resume.ts`, and the launch pipeline itself\n- Browser verification is designed as an additive pipeline step: build runs first, browser tests only run if build passes\n- Browser tests are discovered from `.wombo-browser/tests/` directory or via a custom `testCommand` config option\n\n## Accomplished\n\n### Completed (3 commits made):\n1. **`src/lib/browser.ts`** — Created BrowserManager class with isolated browser instance management: unique user data dirs, unique DevTools ports, headless/headed mode, browser binary auto-detection, test script discovery/execution, screenshot capture, environment variable injection for test scripts\n2. **`src/config.ts`** — Added `BrowserConfig` interface and `browser` section to `WomboConfig` with defaults (enabled: false, headless: true, auto-detect browser, timeouts, viewport)\n3. **`src/lib/browser-verifier.ts`** — Created browser verification bridge: detects browser tests, manages browser lifecycle during verification, produces structured results with error summaries\n4. **`src/lib/verifier.ts`** — Added `FullVerificationResult` type and `runFullVerification()` that chains build + browser verification\n5. **`src/lib/prompt.ts`** — Added browser testing instructions section to agent prompts (when browser.enabled)\n6. **`src/commands/verify.ts`** — Added `browserVerify` option and `--browser` flag support\n7. **`src/commands/launch.ts`** — Updated `handleBuildVerification` to use `runFullVerification` and report browser test results\n\n### In Progress:\n8. **`src/index.ts`** — Need to add `--browser` CLI flag to arg parsing and wire it to verify/launch commands\n\n### Remaining:\n9. **`src/lib/schema.ts`** — Need to add `--browser` flag to verify and launch command schemas in the declarative registry\n10. **Run `bun run build`** — Final verification that everything compiles\n\n## Relevant files / directories\n\n### Created:\n- `src/lib/browser.ts` — BrowserManager class (core browser instance management)\n- `src/lib/browser-verifier.ts` — Bridge between BrowserManager and verification pipeline\n\n### Modified:\n- `src/config.ts` — Added `BrowserConfig` interface and defaults\n- `src/lib/verifier.ts` — Added `FullVerificationResult`, `runFullVerification()`\n- `src/lib/prompt.ts` — Added browser testing section to agent prompts\n- `src/commands/verify.ts` — Added `browserVerify` option\n- `src/commands/launch.ts` — Updated `handleBuildVerification` to use full verification\n\n### Need modification:\n- `src/index.ts` — Add `--browser` flag parsing (CLIArgs interface + parseArgs switch)\n- `src/lib/schema.ts` — Add `--browser` flag to command schema registry\n\n### Key reference files (read but not modified):\n- `src/lib/state.ts` — Wave/agent state types\n- `src/lib/launcher.ts` — Agent process spawning\n- `src/lib/monitor.ts` — Process monitoring\n- `src/lib/worktree.ts` — Git worktree management\n- `src/lib/features.ts` — Feature types and selection\n- `src/lib/output.ts` — Output formatting helpers\n- `src/lib/templates.ts` — Agent template management\n- `package.json` — Project config (build: `bun build src/index.ts --outdir dist --target node`)\n- `tsconfig.json` — TypeScript config (strict, ES2022, bundler moduleResolution)","time":{"start":1773352286994,"end":1773352286994}}}
