{"type":"text","timestamp":1773352342643,"sessionID":"ses_31bfcf566ffeX54k1gNGv0ej46","part":{"id":"prt_ce40945f20026JUQY5inTGwYPZ","sessionID":"ses_31bfcf566ffeX54k1gNGv0ej46","messageID":"msg_ce4093f0e001HzihVJ30MacJ52","type":"text","text":"Now for the launch command — the `--browser` flag should override `config.browser.enabled` before passing config. Let me check how the launch command receives its config. Looking at the launch code, config is passed through and `config.browser.enabled` is used by `runFullVerification`. The cleanest approach is to apply the override at the CLI routing level, similar to how verify does it:","time":{"start":1773352342643,"end":1773352342643}}}
