{"type":"text","timestamp":1773352426275,"sessionID":"ses_31bfcf566ffeX54k1gNGv0ej46","part":{"id":"prt_ce40a685b002sOLgSTzoJ33A4e","sessionID":"ses_31bfcf566ffeX54k1gNGv0ej46","messageID":"msg_ce40a5ed3001bPPdNWdlswDbuY","type":"text","text":"All work is complete. Here's a summary of what was accomplished across 4 commits:\n\n## Final Summary\n\n### Commit 1: `feat(agent-browser-integration): add BrowserManager and browser config`\n- **`src/lib/browser.ts`** — Created `BrowserManager` class with isolated browser instance management (unique user data dirs, unique DevTools ports, headless/headed mode, browser binary auto-detection, test script discovery/execution, screenshot capture, environment variable injection)\n- **`src/config.ts`** — Added `BrowserConfig` interface and `browser` section to `WomboConfig` with sensible defaults (enabled: false, headless: true, auto-detect browser, timeouts, viewport)\n\n### Commit 2: `feat(agent-browser-integration): add browser verification pipeline`\n- **`src/lib/browser-verifier.ts`** — Created browser verification bridge: detects browser tests, manages browser lifecycle, produces structured results with error summaries\n- **`src/lib/verifier.ts`** — Added `FullVerificationResult` type and `runFullVerification()` that chains build + browser verification\n\n### Commit 3: `feat(agent-browser-integration): integrate browser verification into pipeline`\n- **`src/commands/verify.ts`** — Added `browserVerify` option and `--browser` flag support\n- **`src/commands/launch.ts`** — Updated `handleBuildVerification` to use `runFullVerification` and report browser test results\n- **`src/lib/prompt.ts`** — Added browser testing instructions section to agent prompts (when browser.enabled)\n\n### Commit 4: `feat(agent-browser-integration): add --browser CLI flag and schema definitions`\n- **`src/index.ts`** — Added `--browser` CLI flag to arg parsing, wired to verify (via `browserVerify` option) and launch (via config override), updated help text\n- **`src/lib/schema.ts`** — Added `--browser` flag definitions to both launch and verify command schemas\n\n### Architecture\n- Browser verification is additive: build runs first, browser tests only run if build passes\n- Browser tests are discovered from `.wombo-browser/tests/` directory\n- Each agent gets an isolated browser instance (unique user data dir + unique DevTools port)\n- Headless mode is default for CI environments\n- No heavy npm dependencies — uses system-installed browsers via child_process with Chrome DevTools Protocol","time":{"start":1773352426274,"end":1773352426274}}}
